sentences:
I just realized I'm not registered to vote in Orange county, is it too late to do that? | It's *not* too late to register to vote here, but the early voting period is the **last** chance to register to vote in Orange County! | Dropping some resources that can hopefully help :) 

It's *not* too late to register to vote here, but the early voting period is the **last** chance to register to vote in Orange County! | \- Chapel Hill Police non-emergency line         919-968-2760 - 8:30 a.m. to 5 p.m. Monday through Friday     

\- Orange County Health Department         919-245-6111 (messages left after hours will be returned the next business day)         Reporting form: [orangecountync.gov/RegisterComplaint](http://orangecountync.gov/RegisterComplaint)

\- UNC-Chapel Hill Student Conduct Referral Form:     [cm.maxient.com/reportingform.php?UNCChapelHill&layout\_id=23](http://cm.maxient.com/reportingform.php?UNCChapelHill&layout_id=23)

 \- 911 after hours 

&#x200B;

 Source: [https://www.townofchapelhill.org/Home/Components/News/News/16559](https://www.townofchapelhill.org/Home/Components/News/News/16559)

&#x200B;

&#x200B;

Should I share this as its own post or try and publicize this info among students (the ones who are being careful/distant) or do you think everyone already has these info handy? | Does anyone have a link to a list of early voting locations in Orange County?
